<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="563" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d563">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.516/14.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-12-10T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1914-12-09T00:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date><hi rend="italic">; received December
                                    10, 1914.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to our letter of December 8 and telegram to Haiti bank attached
                            to said letter, please substitute for said telegram the following:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>From total gold you hold, retain four hundred thousand dollars
                                    there. Have balance packed for shipment uninsured to Hallgarten
                                    by United States warship. You will be advised later name ship
                                    and date sailing. Cable immediately amount you will ship. Send
                                    by first mail all statements condition bank, also statements
                                    customs receipts since June 30.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wehrhane</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>